Uses of Package
org.sakaiproject.genericdao.api.search

Packages that use org.sakaiproject.genericdao.api.search
org.sakaiproject.genericdao.api.finders These finder interfaces contain additional dependency safe functions which can extend the functionality of the GenericDao. 
org.sakaiproject.genericdao.api.interceptors These annotations allow us to define the link between our persistent classes and the database without configuration files 
org.sakaiproject.genericdao.api.search These search beans contain additional dependency safe classes which can be used for searches and deciding what data to return 
org.sakaiproject.genericdao.base   
org.sakaiproject.genericdao.hibernate These hibernate based generic DAO implementations can either be used directly to handle persistent object operations in an application or extended to meet more specific needs. 
org.sakaiproject.genericdao.springjdbc These spring jdbc based generic DAO implementations can either be used directly to handle persistent object operations in an application or extended to meet more specific needs. 
org.sakaiproject.genericdao.util Utilities which support JDBC and a few other misc things which assist with the generic dao 
 

Classes in org.sakaiproject.genericdao.api.search used by org.sakaiproject.genericdao.api.finders
Search
          This is a simple class which allows the passing of a set of search parameters in a nice way
Example usage:
Search s1 = new Search("title", curTitle); // search where title equals value of curTitle
Search s2 = new Search("title", curTitle, Restriction.NOT_EQUALS); // search where title not equals value of curTitle
Search s2 = new Search(
new Restriction("title", curTitle),
new Order("title")
); // search where title equals value of curTitle and order is by title ascending

Most searches can be modeled this way fairly easily.

Classes in org.sakaiproject.genericdao.api.search used by org.sakaiproject.genericdao.api.search
Order
          A simple bean which defines the order to return the results of a search
Example usage:
Order ota = new Order("title"); // order by title ascending
Order otd = new Order("title", false); // order by title descending
Restriction
          A simple bean which defines a restriction in a search, this is like saying: where userId = '123'; OR where userId like '%aaronz%';
Example usage:
Restriction rteq = new Restriction("title", curTitle); // restrict search to title equals value of curTitle
Restriction rtne = new Restriction("title", curTitle, Restriction.NOT_EQUALS); // restrict search to title not equals value of curTitle
Search
          This is a simple class which allows the passing of a set of search parameters in a nice way
Example usage:
